        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(harness): avoid default Codex pre-tool loop relay",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes an unnecessary Codex Harness native PreToolUse relay in the default configuration.\n\n`tools.loopDetection.enabled` is documented and typed as default `false`, but `nativePreToolUseMayRunLoopDetection()` treated an unset loop-detection config as enabled via `enabled !== false`. For Codex Harness, that made the runtime install a native PreToolUse hook whenever a session key existed, even when the user had not enabled tool-loop detection and no before-tool policy needed to run.\n\nBecause Codex executes native hooks as `openclaw hooks relay` subprocesses, the default path added OpenClaw-side CPU overhead on tool-heavy Codex Harness runs. Codex ACP does not use this same Codex native-hook relay path, which explains part of the Harness-vs-ACP CPU delta.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Treat native loop-detection PreToolUse relay work as present only when `tools.loopDetection.enabled === true`.\n- Preserve PreToolUse relay behavior for explicit `before_tool_call` policy/trusted policy work.\n- Preserve PreToolUse relay behavior when loop detection is explicitly enabled.\n- Keep explicit `enabled: false` behavior unchanged.\n\n## Evidence\n\nOpenClaw 2026.5.28 CPU probe, same Codex Harness leaf, same prompt/model/runtime, 60s window, corrected sampler excluding sampler/ps overhead:\n\n| Run | tick CPU-s | pcpu integral CPU-s | OpenClaw CLI CPU-s | OpenClaw hooks CPU-s | OpenClaw agent CPU-s |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |\n| Harness default | 9.25 | 26.320 | 3.16 | 0.44 | 3.96 |\n| Harness with `tools.loopDetection.enabled=false` | 6.82 | 23.488 | 1.07 | 0.00 | 3.88 |\n\nInterpretation:\n\n- Disabling loop detection removed visible `openclaw-hooks` relay samples and reduced `openclaw-cli` CPU by about 66% in this 60s probe.\n- The persistent `openclaw-agent` CPU did not materially change, so this patch targets the avoidable native-hook relay subprocess work, not the Harness agent wait-loop baseline.\n- A copied-leaf patched runtime probe was not used as proof because copied `plugins/installs.json` retained absolute plugin install paths from the source leaf; the source-level tests below are the authoritative validation for this patch.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts` -> 2 files passed, 152 tests passed.\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.turn-watches.test.ts` -> 3 files passed, 217 tests passed.\n- `git diff --check` -> passed.\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/codex-harness-loop-detection-relay-default",
